A person shall not—
sell, move, or present for slaughter or any other purpose, ananimalthat is not identified in accordance with this Act;
sell, move, or present for another purpose, ananimal productoranimal by-productthat is not identified in accordance with this Act;
process ananimal,animal productoranimal by-productthat is not identified in accordance with this Act; or
exhibit, store, distribute, import or export, or market ananimal,animal productoranimal by-productthat is not identified in accordance with this Act.

A person is eligible to be registered as anagentif that person is—
a citizen or holder of a residence permit;
domiciled in the Republic;
notlegally disqualifiedfrom performing the functions of anagent;
not an undischarged bankrupt; and
not a body corporate.

TheTraceability Officermay suspend or cancel anagent certificateif the holder—
does not comply with the terms and conditions of theagent certificate;
islegally disqualifiedfrom performing the functions of theagent;
obtained theagent certificatethrough fraud, misrepresentation or concealment of a material fact;
is convicted of fraud, forgery or uttering a forged document; or
is convicted of an offence under this Act.

TheTraceability Officershall keep and maintain registers of—
owners of animals,animalproducts andanimalby-products;
agents;
the holders of premises certificates,animal identification markcertificates andagentcertificates;
cancelled premises certificates,animal identificationcertificates andagentcertificates;
animal identificationmarks; and
any other information that theTraceability Officermay determine.
The registers referred to under subsection(1)shall contain particulars that may be prescribed.
The registers shall be kept in the custody of theTraceability Officerat the offices of theTraceability Officerand shall be open for inspection to members of the public during normal office hours on payment of a fee that theTraceability Officermay determine.
TheTraceability Officershall, on an application made by a person as prescribed, issue to the person a certified extract from the register or a copy of a certificate as prescribed, on payment of a fee as theTraceability Officermay determine.

